    <!-- Dashboard Help Content -->
    <string name="help_dashboard_step1_title">1. Your \'Safe to Spend\' Limit</string>
    <string name="help_dashboard_step1_desc">This is your daily financial compass. Monetra calculates exactly how much cash you can spend TODAY to survive the month successfully while hitting your savings goal. It dynamically subtracts Fixed Bills, Loans, and Categories. Just stay below this number!</string>
    <string name="help_dashboard_step2_title">2. Liquid Bar &amp; Overspending</string>
    <string name="help_dashboard_step2_desc">The Progress Bar visually shows your spending threshold. If you overspend today, Monetra instantly borrows money from your TOMORROW\'S daily limit. It enforces discipline by strictly locking your remaining spending rhythm.</string>
    <string name="help_dashboard_step3_title">3. Monthly Health &amp; Insights</string>
    <string name="help_dashboard_step3_desc">Observe the \'Waterfall\' breakdown below the Safe to Spend card. Monetra automatically takes your monthly income, strips away Debt EMIs, strips away your Fixed Bills, locks your Savings Goal, and gives you real visibility over your Free Cash.</string>

    <!-- Assistant Help Content -->
    <string name="help_assistant_step1_title">1. Impact Checker</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step1_desc">Before you make any impulse purchase, use the Impact Checker. Enter the item\'s price, and the Assistant will simulate the effect on your wealth. It verifies if you have the buffer to buy it without hurting your goals.</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step2_title">2. Reading the Verdict</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step2_desc">🟢 Safe: Buy it! No impact on your savings.\n🟡 Savings Risk: This threatens your monthly savings goal.\n🔴 Big Purchase!: This costs significant days of your life\'s earnings and will drain your emergency stash.</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step3_title">3. Daily Pocket Money Tracking</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step3_desc">Strictly follow the \'Pocket Money\' boundary given. If you remain within this Goldilocks range, you are Mathematically Guaranteed to hit your monthly savings goal.</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step4_title">4. Essential Stash (Runway)</string>
    <string name="help_assistant_step4_desc">Your Financial Runway is calculated using [Total Liquid Cash] ÷ [Fixed Bills + Survival Spend]. It highlights exactly how many months you can survive if your income abruptly stops. Target: 6 to 9 months.</string>

    <!-- Transactions Help Content -->
    <string name="help_transactions_step1_title">1. Log Spends Quickly</string>
    <string name="help_transactions_step1_desc">Tap the floating \'+\' button to record new transactions instantly. Ensure you categorize them correctly (e.g., Food, Travel) so the Dashboard and Monthly Report can generate accurate spending patterns.</string>
    <string name="help_transactions_step2_title">2. Swipe-to-Delete Timeline</string>
    <string name="help_transactions_step2_desc">Want to delete an accidental entry? Just swipe left on the entry! A massive, premium \"Mark Delete\" UI will emerge. Best part? Monetra offers an immediate \"Undo\" snackbar just in case you swipe by mistake.</string>

    <!-- Simulator Help Content -->
    <string name="help_simulator_step1_title">1. \'What-If\' Financial Scenarios</string>
    <string name="help_simulator_step1_desc">Thinking of a new job? Wondering what happens if you take an expensive Car Loan? Enter these \"What If\" values into the simulator to test life decisions digitally before making them.</string>
    <string name="help_simulator_step2_title">2. 12-Month Reality Projection</string>
    <string name="help_simulator_step2_desc">Monetra\'s algorithm calculates the exact impact of your \'What-If\' scenario over the next 365 days. It will warn you if taking that loan pushes you into \"CRITICAL\" EMI stress limits.</string>

    <!-- Loans Help Content -->
    <string name="help_loans_step1_title">1. Your Unified Debt Tracker</string>
    <string name="help_loans_step1_desc">Add all active EMIs, Personal, and Home Loans here. Monetra prioritizes these as \"Committed Expenditures\" and removes them directly from your Salary before calculating anything else.</string>

    <!-- Investments Help Content -->
    <string name="help_investments_step1_title">1. Setup Your Portfolio</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step1_desc">Navigate to the Portfolio Screen to set up your current financial reality. Add your total Savings, total Investment Value, and total Loan Debts to calculate your true Net Worth instantly.</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step2_title">2. Financial Score Nudges</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step2_desc">Monetra reviews your Portfolio to give you a Financial Health Score (Poor to Excellent). Nudges will warn you if too much money is sitting idly in cash or if your loan obligations represent a dangerous percentage.</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step3_title">3. Track Free Money</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step3_desc">The \"Free Money\" card is your liquidity indicator. It calculates what extra cash is comfortably available AFTER clearing off all loans, budgets, and investments limits. Positive means you are thriving.</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step4_title">4. Manage Portfolios Faster</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step4_desc">Use the highly accessible \"Manage\" chips block at the bottom of the Portfolio Screen to instantly jump into your specific Loan logs, Expense logs, and Investment profiles.</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step5_title">5. Wealth Projection Simulator</string>
    <string name="help_investments_step5_desc">Analyze exactly how rich you will be down the line. Add your expected Return on Investment %, enter your projection horizon in years, and watch how Compound Interest exponentially grows your Net Worth over a decade.</string>

    <!-- Fixed Costs Help Content -->
    <string name="help_fixed_costs_step1_title">1. Handle Monthly Obligations</string>
    <string name="help_fixed_costs_step1_desc">Log your Rent, Electricity, Internet bills, and subscriptions here. Unlike daily spending, these are automatically \"reserved\" off the top of your salary to prevent you from accidentally burning money needed for housing.</string>

    <!-- Refundable Help Content -->
    <string name="help_refundable_guide_title">Refundables Guide</string>
    <string name="help_refundable_step1_title">1. Track Money Owed</string>
    <string name="help_refundable_step1_desc">Did you lend money to a friend? Did you pay for team lunch? Track those \"To Be Refunded\" entries here safely. They won\'t pollute your actual expense log.</string>
    <string name="help_refundable_step2_title">2. Swipe Filters &amp; Paid Management</string>
    <string name="help_refundable_step2_desc">Smoothly swipe left or right to switch between \"Pending\", \"Paid\", or \"Overdue\" tabs. Need to mark an item as collected? Just swipe the individual row to instantly mark it as Paid and return the money to your Dashboard.</string>

    <!-- Budgets Help Content -->
    <string name="help_budgets_guide_title">Budgets Guide</string>
    <string name="help_budgets_step1_title">1. Granular Spend Caps</string>
    <string name="help_budgets_step1_desc">Allocate explicit spending ceilings for Food, Fun, Transport, and Shopping. Monetra dynamically enforces these caps throughout your app, throwing warnings if you approach the specified boundary.</string>
    <string name="help_budgets_step2_title">2. Category Isolation</string>
    <string name="help_budgets_step2_desc">Instead of guessing where your money goes, Budgets gives you progress bars specifically for those high-leakage categories. Easily distinguish if your \"Food\" limit is failing while your \"Shopping\" is safe.</string>

